{"word":"νεάζω","slug":"νεάζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νεάζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νέος'><el>νέος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>, <a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to be young</i> or <i>new</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>τὸ νεάζον</el> <i>youth</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>νεάζων</el> <i>thinking</i> or <i>acting like a youth</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be the younger of two</i>, <el>ὁ μὲν νεάζων</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to grow young</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}